cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on autonomous vehicles navigating in dynamic environments with pedestrians. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper mentions onboard sensor/perception data being used to predict pedestrian motion patterns. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses unsupervised learning of a Gaussian process mixture model to cluster pedestrian motion patterns. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of predictive modeling to assess future intentions of dynamic agents. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of a chance-constrained motion planner to identify safe trajectories.
